race.comment: KRAKEN MILLY (1) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten 2 lengths, (25.71) at this track. Deserves serious consideration. AUNTIE AMBER (4) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (28.75) last time in a Grade 5 at Bendigo. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. TWILIGHT AXLE (6) struggled in tougher grade last start after losing his position early at this track, but prior to that won by 1.3 lengths at this track (22.37) beating Dookie Giblet in a Grade 5 on October 16. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. ROCK SHOW (2) is in the mix after placing last time out.
